HEADWORD: manna lichen
<hw>manna lichen</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>Any of several Old World
semicrustaceous or shrubby lecanoras that roll up and are blown about
over African and Arabian deserts and used as food by people and animals;
same as <er>manna</er>{2}.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

